  "explanation": "In determining the appropriate sentence, several factors were considered. The defendant is a first-time offender with no prior criminal record, which strongly mitigates the severity of the punishment. Furthermore, the defendant has already made an effort to partially repay the embezzled $25,000, demonstrating a degree of remorse and a willingness to make the victim whole. Embezzlement is a serious breach of trust, especially for an accountant, warranting some punitive measure to serve as a deterrent. The outburst from the spectator demanding a 10-year sentence is emotional and has no legal bearing or influence on this court's decision. Balancing the breach of professional fiduciary duty with the mitigating factors of a clean prior record and ongoing restitution, a brief period of incarceration followed by supervised probation to ensure full repayment is the most appropriate and just outcome.",
  "verdict": 6
